Utterance: Hi again! It's great to see you back. How have you been since our last session?
I've been doing pretty well, thanks! Just keeping busy with work and life.
That’s good to hear! Last time, you mentioned feeling relaxed and invigorated after your day at the beach. Have you had a chance to spend more time outdoors since then?
Yes, actually! I went hiking last weekend. It felt amazing to be in nature again.
That sounds wonderful! How did that experience make you feel?
It was refreshing. I felt more connected and grounded.
That’s great! It seems like nature really has a positive impact on you. Have you thought about incorporating more outdoor activities into your routine?
I have! I’m trying to set aside time every week for something outdoors.
That’s a fantastic goal. How do you think that will affect your overall well-being?
I think it’ll help me feel less stressed and more energized. Just being outside really lifts my mood.
Absolutely. It sounds like you’re recognizing the importance of self-care. Have you been practicing your meditation and yoga as well?
Yes, I’ve been consistent with that. It really helps me center myself.
Wonderful! What specific benefits have you noticed from those practices?
I feel calmer and more focused. It’s easier to handle stress when I meditate regularly.
That’s a valuable insight. It sounds like you have some solid coping strategies in place. Have you faced any challenges in your daily life that you’d like to discuss?
Well, I’ve been feeling a bit overwhelmed with work lately.
I see. Can you tell me more about what’s causing that feeling of overwhelm?
It’s just a lot of clients and projects piling up, and I’m worried I won’t be able to keep up.
That’s understandable. It’s common to feel that way when responsibilities increase. Have you considered any strategies to manage that workload?
I’ve thought about prioritizing tasks and maybe delegating some responsibilities.
That’s a great approach! Prioritizing can certainly help. How do you feel about asking for help from others?
I sometimes struggle with that. I don’t want to seem like I can’t handle things.
It’s completely normal to feel that way, but asking for help can be a sign of strength. How do you think it would feel to reach out for support when needed?
I guess it would relieve some stress, but I still feel hesitant.
It’s important to acknowledge those feelings. Perhaps we can work on building your confidence in asking for help. Would you like to explore that?
Yeah, I think that would be helpful.
Great! Let’s start by identifying small steps you could take to practice this. What’s one small task you could delegate or ask for help with?
Maybe I could ask a colleague to help with some client follow-ups.
That sounds like a perfect start! How would you feel about approaching them?
I think I could do it. It would be a relief to share some of the workload.
That’s a positive mindset! Let’s set that as a goal for this week. How about we check in on how that goes next time?
Sounds good!
Wonderful. Before we wrap up, is there anything else on your mind that you’d like to discuss?
Just thinking about how to balance work and personal life better.
That’s an important topic. Maybe we can explore some time management strategies next session.
I’d like that.
Perfect! I’m looking forward to hearing about your progress with asking for help and any insights you have about work-life balance.
Me too!
Thank you for sharing today. Take care, and I’ll see you next time!
Goodbye!
